4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, Alabama is an open primary
6 state. There is no requirement in state law that an
7 elector must register his or her party affiliation when
8 registering to vote.
9 This bill would allow an elector to register a
10 political party affiliation.
11 This bill would require an elector to be
12 registered with a political party in order to vote that
13 party's ballot in a primary election or primary runoff
14 election.
15 This bill would prohibit an elector from
16 switching his or her political party affiliation to
17 another political party during a blackout period
18 starting 60 says before a primary election.
19 This bill would require the Secretary of State
20 to update the voter registration form, retain certain
21 voter history, and adopt rules.
22 This bill would also require each political
23 party to publish qualifications for candidates on its
24 official website.
25 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
26 technical revisions to update the existing code
27 language to current style.
28
