120 "§17-3-52
121 (a) The board of registrars shall have power to
122 examine, under oath or affirmation, all applicants for
123 registration, and to may take testimony touching the
124 qualifications of such applicants, but no applicant shall be
125 required to answer any question, written or oral, not related
126 to his or her qualifications to register.
127 (b)(1) In order to aid the registrars to judicially
128 determine if applicants to register have the qualifications to
129 register to vote, each applicant shall be furnished by the
130 board a written application, which shall be uniform in all
131 cases with no discrimination as between applicants., the The
132 form and contents of which the application shall be
133 promulgated adopted, by rule, by the Secretary of State of the
134 State of Alabama. The application shall be so worded that
135 there will be placed before the registrars information
136 necessary or proper to aid them the registrars to pass upon
137 the qualifications of each applicant. The application shall be
138 completed in writing. There shall be incorporated in such
139 application an oath to support and defend the Constitution of
140 the United States and the Constitution of the State of Alabama
