180 "§17-13-1
181 A primary election, including a separate and special
182 presidential preference primary election, within the meaning
183 of this chapter, is an election held by the qualified voters
184 who are registered members of any political party, for the
185 purpose of nominating a candidate or candidates for public or
186 party office."
187 "§17-13-7
188 (a) All persons individuals who are qualified electors
189 under the general laws of the State of Alabama and who are
190 also registered members of a political party and entitled to
191 participate in such primary election under the rules of the
192 party shall be entitled to vote therein in a primary election
193 or primary runoff election and shall receive the official
194 primary ballot of that political party for which he or she is
195 registered pursuant to Section 1., and no other; but every
196 governing body of a party shall have the right, power, and
