"§17-13-47
HB541 INTRODUCED
225 (a) The governing body of a political party may fix
226 assessments upon those able to pay, or other qualifications as
227 it may deem necessary, for persons individuals desiring to
228 become candidates for nomination to offices at a primary
229 election, but such assessments shall not exceed two percent of
230 one year's salary of the office sought and, for an
231 unremunerative or party county office or an unremunerative or
232 party office to be filled by a vote of a subdivision greater
233 than one county, it shall not exceed fifty dollars ($50) or
234 one hundred fifty dollars ($150) for an unremunerative or
235 party office to be filled by a vote of the entire state.
236 (b) The governing body of each political party shall
237 publish on its official website the qualifications set by the
238 governing body for candidates seeking nomination to offices of
239 that political party."
240 Section 3. Section 17-13-7.1, Code of Alabama 1975,
241 prohibiting crossover voting between a primary election and
242 subsequent primary runoff election, is repealed.
243 Section 4. This act shall become effective on January
244 1, 2027.
